        <h3>What Does "Internal Use" Mean?</h3>
        <p>Your routine business within your organization. Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>For U.S. Government agencies</strong>, "internal" means the whole of the U.S. Government. One agency may provide Marque-based services to another agency without a commercial license.</li>
          <li><strong>For corporations</strong>, "internal" includes the corporation and its wholly owned subsidiaries.</li>
          <li><strong>For contractors providing direct support</strong> to an organization that uses Marque, use in the course of that support is considered internal use of the supported organization.</li>
          <li><strong>For personal use</strong>, you may use, study, modify, and build on Marque for your own non-commercial purposes. The modification-tracking requirement does not apply to personal use.</li>
          <li><strong>For foreign governments</strong>, "internal" means a country's entire national government.</li>
          <li><strong>For international organizations</strong>, "internal" means within the organization's routine business. NATO, for example, may use, modify, or integrate Marque on NATO systems. "Internal" does not extend to member nations' own systems.</li>
