        <h2>FAQ</h2>

        <p><strong>I'm a contractor on an agency contract. The agency's systems include Marque. Can I use it?</strong></p>
        <p>Yes. You can use Marque in a way materially similar to the agency's employees — as part of the agency's routine business. This is internal use.</p>

        <p><strong>My company is building a product for a Government agency and wants to include Marque. Do we need a commercial license?</strong></p>
        <p>Yes. If Marque is part of something you're delivering to someone else — even the Government — that's external use. Contact <a href="mailto:licensing@knitli.com">licensing@knitli.com</a>.</p>

        <p><strong>Can I use Marque for personal projects?</strong></p>
